name: r-essentials
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "r-essentials" %}

package:
  name: {{ name }}
  version: {{ r_base }}

build:
  noarch: generic
  # r-rbokeh is not available under Windows
  number: 2002

requirements:
  host:
    - r-base
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-recommended
    - r-ggplot2 >=3.1.0
    - r-plyr >=1.8.4
    - r-reshape2 >=1.4.3
    - r-dplyr >=0.7.8
    - r-tidyr >=0.8.1
    - r-caret >=6.0_80
    - r-randomforest >=4.6_14
    - r-data.table >=1.11.8
    - r-quantmod >=0.4_13
    - r-shiny >=1.2.0
    - r-rmarkdown >=1.10
    - r-glmnet >=2.0_16
    - r-jsonlite >=1.5
    - r-zoo >=1.8_3
    - r-irkernel >=0.8.14
    - r-rbokeh >=0.5.0
    - r-formatr >=1.5
    - notebook >=5.7.2
    - r-tidyverse >=1.2.1
    - r-dbi >=1.0.0
    - r-broom >=0.5.0
    - r-forcats >=0.3.0
    - r-haven >=1.1.2
    - r-hms >=0.4.2
    - r-httr >=1.3.1
    - r-lubridate >=1.7.4
    - r-magrittr >=1.5
    - r-modelr >=0.1.2
    - r-purrr >=0.2.5
    - r-readr >=1.1.1
    - r-readxl >=1.1.0
    - r-rvest >=0.3.2
    - r-stringr >=1.3.1
    - r-tibble >=1.4.2
    - r-xml2 >=1.2.0

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('ggplot2')"  # [not win]
    - $R -e "library('tibble')"  # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('ggplot2')\""  # [win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('tibble')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://github.com/conda-forge/r-essentials-feedstock
  license: MIT
  license_family: MIT
  summary: Some essential packages for working with R. This was migrated from the 'r' channel.
  license_file:
    - {{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/MIT

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
